  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Jeremiah 7:20",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jeremiah 7:20",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Therefore thus saith the Lord ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— And what he saith he will not unsay, nor can all the world withstand its execution. Hear it therefore and tremble. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Behold, mine anger and my fury shall be poured out upon this place ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— As the flood of waters was poured upon the old world, or the shower of fire and brimstone upon Sodom; since they will provoke me, let them feel the effects of their conduct. They shall soon find, 1st, That there is no escaping this deluge of wrath, either by fleeing from it, or fencing against it. It shall be poured out on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "this place ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Though it be a holy place, the Lord’s house. It shall reach both ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "man and beast ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Like the plagues of Egypt; and, like some of them, shall destroy the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "trees of the field and the fruit of the ground — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Which they had designed and prepared for Baal, and of which they had made ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cakes to the queen of heaven. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They shall find, 2d, That there is no extinguishing it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "it shall burn and shall not be quenched",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " — Prayers and tears, forms and ceremonies of worship, and ritual observances of whatever kind, shall then avail nothing, to prevent that total destruction which it shall produce.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "7:17-20 The Jews took pride in showing zeal for their idols. Let us learn to be earnest in the service of our God, even from this bad example. Let us think it an honour to be employed in any work for God. Let us be as diligent ourselves, and as careful to teach our children the truths of God, as many are to teach the mysteries of iniquity. The direct tendency of this sin is malice against God, but it will hurt themselves. And they shall find there is no escaping. God's wrath is fire unquenchable.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
